<html>

<head>
	<h1>Recipe For Crisco Cookies</h1>
</head>

<body>
	<h2>Ingredients</h2>
	
	<p><ul>
		<li>3/4 stick of <a href="http://www.crisco.com/recipes/" target="_blank">Crisco</a> Vegetable Shortning</li>
		<li>1 <sup>1/4</sup> cup of light brown sugar</li>
		<li>2 tblsp of <a href="http://www.milka.com/" target="_blank">milk</a></li>
		<li>2 tsp vanilla extract</li>
		<li>1 large egg</li>
		<li>1 <sup>3/4</sup> cup of flour</li>
		<li>1 tsp of <a href="http://www.ci.slc.ut.us/" target="_blank">salt</a></li>
		<li>3/4 tsp of baking soda</li>
		<li>1 cup of <a href="http://www.nestleusa.com/brands/Baking/Toll-House-Morsels" target="_blank">milk chocolate chips</a></li>
	</ul></p>

	<h2>Baking Instructions</h2>
	
	<p><ol>
			<li>Pre-heat oven to 375 degrees.</li>
			<li>Mix dry ingredients, i.e. flour, baking soda, and salt.</li>
			<li>In another bowl mix wet ingredients, i.e. <a href="http://www.crisco.com/products/all-vegetable-shortening-17-315" target="_blank">shortening</a>, brown sugar, milk, and vanilla extract.</li>
			<li>Beat wet mixture until creamy, then add the <a href="http://www.crisco.com/the-crisco-kitchen/cooking-how-to/how-to-cook-everything/cooking-with-eggs.aspx" target="_blank">egg</a>.</li>
			<li>Combine dry mixture into wet mixture by thirds until completely incorporated and add half of the chocolate chips.</li>
			<li>Lightly flour the other 1/2 cup of chocolate chips, then add to the mixture and stir.</li>
			<li>Take a <a href="http://www.crisco.com/products/butter-spray-16-314" target="_blank">lightly oiled</a> cookie sheet, and place a spoonful of cookie dough 3 inches apart. One batch makes about 3 dozen.</li>
			<li>Place in center rack, and bake for 12 minutes. At the six minute mark turn cookie sheet for even baking!</li>
			<li>Once out, let cookies sit for a couple of minutes, then move cookies to a cooling rack until they cool down completely.</li>
			<li>Finally, eat cookies or freeze them for later.</li>
	</ol></p>

	<p>Email <a href="mailto:beth.goss@gordon.edu">Beth Goss</a> for more information!</p>



</body>
</html>
